[{"id":"AGENTS.md#0","metadata":{"content":"# Agentes de IA — empiecen acá\n\nEste repositorio usa la metodología **KDD (Knowledge-Driven Development)**. Las reglas obligatorias completas están en [.agents/AGENTS.md](.agents/AGENTS.md) y la skill local en [.agents/skills/kdd-okf-ccdd-hybrid/SKILL.md](.agents/skills/kdd-okf-ccdd-hybrid/SKILL.md).\n\nAntes de escribir código: lee los contratos en `knowledge/contracts/` y valida con `python scripts/validate_contracts.py knowledge/contracts`. Este archivo es un puente, no duplica contenido.","okf_concept":"AGENTS.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"Agentes de IA — empiecen acá"}},{"id":"BENCHMARKS.md#0","metadata":{"content":"# Benchmarks\n\nDos cosas distintas y honestamente etiquetadas:\n\n1. **Benchmark del gate** — determinista, reproducible en cualquier máquina. Es un benchmark de verdad.\n2. **Economía con modelos** — *ilustrativo*, no riguroso (N pequeño, una corrida, atado a tu hardware/modelo/precios). No es un leaderboard.\n\n---\n\n## 1. Gate determinista (reproducible)\n\n`python benchmarks/bench_gate.py` — sin LLM, sin red, mismo resultado corrida a corrida.\n\n| Operación | Costo | Tokens |\n|---|---|---|\n| `metrics.functions_metrics` (AST) | ~0.28 ms/op | 0 |\n| `tc_lint.lint` (valida un task-contract) | ~0.71 ms/op | 0 |\n| `task_gate.gate` (veredicto pleno: lint + complejidad + tests) | ~81 ms/op | 0 |","okf_concept":"BENCHMARKS.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"Benchmarks"}},{"id":"BENCHMARKS.md#1","metadata":{"content":"o: lint + complejidad + tests) | ~81 ms/op | 0 |\n\n*Medido en Windows, Python 3.14, una corrida. Reproducí con el script; los números absolutos\nvarían por máquina, el orden de magnitud no.*\n\n**Lectura honesta:** la **lógica del gate** (métricas + lint) es **sub-milisegundo**. Los ~81 ms\ndel veredicto pleno son **ejecutar tus property-tests congelados** (aquí 500 iteraciones por test\nen un subproceso) — algo que correrías igual. El veredicto en sí no agrega costo perceptible.\n\n**El punto:** la verificación que en un loop agéntico sería una *review por LLM* (~1–2k tokens de\nentrada + segundos de latencia + costo de API, y **no determinista**) aquí es **0 tokens, sin red,\ny byte-idéntica**. Eso es lo que el gate reemplaza.\n\n---","okf_concept":"BENCHMARKS.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"Benchmarks"}},{"id":"BENCHMARKS.md#2","metadata":{"content":"éntica**. Eso es lo que el gate reemplaza.\n\n---\n\n## 2. Economía grande/pequeño vs loop de modelo grande (ILUSTRATIVO)\n\nLote real corrido con `runners/measure.py` sobre 4 task-contracts (`clamp`, `popcount`,\n`hamming`, `chunk`), implementador **gemma-4-12b** local (LM Studio), escalado a un modelo mayor.\n\n**Resultado de implementación:** 4/4 PASS **al primer intento**, **0 escalados**.\n\n| Métrica | Nuestro flujo | Loop de modelo grande |\n|---|---|---|\n| Implementación (4 tasks) | $0 (modelo local) | incluido abajo |\n| Validación / veredicto | $0 (gate determinista) | — (no tiene; el modelo se auto-juzga) |\n| **Solo el loop** | **$0** | **~$0.138** |\n\n→ Solo el loop: **100% de ahorro de API.** Pero ese titular **no es la cuenta completa.**","okf_concept":"BENCHMARKS.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"Benchmarks"}},{"id":"BENCHMARKS.md#3","metadata":{"content":"* Pero ese titular **no es la cuenta completa.**\n\n**Costo total honesto (incluyendo autoría + auditoría, que van en el modelo grande):**\n\n| | Nuestro flujo (1ª vez) | Loop de modelo grande |\n|---|---|---|\n| Autoría contrato+tests (grande) | ~$0.26 | — |\n| Auditoría de tests (grande) | ~$0.13 | — |\n| Implementación + veredicto | $0 | ~$0.138 |\n| **TOTAL primera vez** | **~$0.38** | **~$0.138** |\n\n→ En tareas **triviales de un tiro, este flujo es ~2.8× MÁS caro.** El overhead fijo\n(autoría + auditoría) se amortiza a **~3 ejecuciones** (regresión, CI, re-implementación):\ndesde ahí, cada re-corrida es $0 vs ~$0.138.","okf_concept":"BENCHMARKS.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"Benchmarks"}},{"id":"BENCHMARKS.md#4","metadata":{"content":"):\ndesde ahí, cada re-corrida es $0 vs ~$0.138.\n\n### Salvedades (léelas antes de citar cualquier número)\n- **N=4, una sola corrida, modelo y hardware específicos.** No es estadística.\n- **Precios ilustrativos** ($15/$75 por millón in/out del modelo grande); ajustá a tu proveedor.\n- **No se cuenta el cómputo local** del modelo pequeño (real, barato, no es token de API).\n- El ahorro **gana por volumen, reuso y dificultad** — NO en el one-shot trivial.\n- El gate es tan fuerte como sus property-tests; tests laxos → \"ahorro\" ilusorio.","okf_concept":"BENCHMARKS.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"Benchmarks"}},{"id":"BENCHMARKS.md#5","metadata":{"content":"operty-tests; tests laxos → \"ahorro\" ilusorio.\n\n### Reproducir\n```bash\npython runners/measure.py examples/batch/*/task.md \\\n  --provider openai --model <tu-modelo-chico> \\\n  --escalate-provider ollama --escalate-model <tu-modelo-grande>\n```\n`measure.py` registra intentos, escalados y tokens por tier, y calcula el costo con tus precios.\n\n---\n\n## 3. Audits project-wide (reproducible)\n\n`audit_annotations` y `audit_composition` barren todos los contratos de un proyecto. Dos\noptimizaciones (commit `5e06e6e`) reducen el costo de los escenarios patológicos sin cambiar el\nresultado (ni el orden de `failures`):","okf_concept":"BENCHMARKS.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"Benchmarks"}},{"id":"BENCHMARKS.md#6","metadata":{"content":"ambiar el\nresultado (ni el orden de `failures`):\n\n- **`audit_annotations` — memoización por target.** Si N contratos apuntan al mismo target, la\n  versión ingenua re-leía y re-parseaba (AST + walk de anotaciones) el archivo una vez por\n  contrato. La cache memoiza por `(target, language)`: leer+parsear UNA vez por target único.\n- **`audit_composition` — hoist O(N²)→O(N).** `_imported_stems(target)` se evaluaba dentro de la\n  comprensión `s for s in funcs if s in _imported_stems(target)` → O(N) parseos por stem → O(N²).\n  Hoist fuera de la comprensión: un parseo por stem.\n\nEscenario sintético (tempdir borrado al final; mediana de 3 corridas; versión actual del repo,\nWindows/Python 3.14):","okf_concept":"BENCHMARKS.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"Benchmarks"}},{"id":"BENCHMARKS.md#7","metadata":{"content":"versión actual del repo,\nWindows/Python 3.14):\n\n| Audit | Escenario | Tiempo actual |\n|---|---|---|\n| `audit_annotations` | 400 contratos → 1 mismo target (200 funciones anotadas) | ~340 ms |\n| `audit_composition` | 150 contratos con imports cruzados (cada target importa 2 otros, 8 fns) | ~210 ms |","okf_concept":"BENCHMARKS.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"Benchmarks"}},{"id":"BENCHMARKS.md#8","metadata":{"content":"(cada target importa 2 otros, 8 fns) | ~210 ms |\n\nSpeedup medido en el commit `5e06e6e`: **~20x** (`audit_annotations`) y **~29x**\n(`audit_composition`). La versión pre-optimización ya no está en el repo, así que esos factores\nse citan de aquel commit (no se re-midieron aquí); el tiempo absoluto de arriba es la referencia\nactual. Validación: reconstruir el loop naïve inline (sin tocar código del repo) reproduce el\norden de magnitud — ~21x en `audit_annotations` (coherente con ~20x); en `audit_composition` el\nfactor escala con el costo de parseo del target, por lo que ~29x es la cifra del commit sobre su\nescenario y targets más pesados lo amplifican.","okf_concept":"BENCHMARKS.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"Benchmarks"}},{"id":"README.md#0","metadata":{"content":"# ccdd-gate\n\n[![PyPI](https://img.shields.io/pypi/v/ccdd-gate)](https://pypi.org/project/ccdd-gate/)\n[![tests](https://github.com/MauricioPerera/ccdd-gate/actions/workflows/test.yml/badge.svg)](https://github.com/MauricioPerera/ccdd-gate/actions/workflows/test.yml)\n[![License: MIT](https://img.shields.io/badge/License-MIT-yellow.svg)](LICENSE)\n\n🌐 **[Landing page](https://mauricioperera.github.io/ccdd-gate/)** — un recorrido visual del método (toggle EN/ES/PT).\n\n**Gates deterministas que mantienen honesto al código escrito por IA.**\nUn modelo pequeño implementa; un árbitro que no se puede sobornar decide si pasó.","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#1","metadata":{"content":"rbitro que no se puede sobornar decide si pasó.\n\nNo es otro loop \"dale al modelo grande hasta que diga que está listo\". La condición de\nparada no es el juicio del modelo —es un veredicto determinista: **complejidad ≤ budget\nfirmado + property-tests congelados que el implementador no puede ablandar**. Mismo input,\nmismo veredicto, corrida a corrida.\n\nEl mismo principio cubre **dos pilares**:","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#10","metadata":{"content":"que no se puede engañar.\n\n## Qué hay acá","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#100","metadata":{"content":".","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#101","metadata":{"content":"AST puro | no |\n| `runners/rules_gate.py` | Aplica los checks deterministas **project-wide por glob** desde un `rules.yaml` (idea declarativa estilo autorules, árbitro AST sin LLM) | no |\n| `runners/linter_gate.py` | Envuelve **linters externos deterministas** como checks opt-in desde un `linters.yaml` (hermano de `rules_gate`, pero el veredicto lo emite un lexterno pineado, no AST propio); hoy solo adaptador `ruff` (dep opcional, no del paquete) | no |\n| `runners/audit_composition.py` | Auditor project-wide: composición sin gatear (función importa a otra sin `kind:group`); distingue deuda de FORMA vs de COMPORTAMIENTO | no |\n| `runners/audit_orphan_targets.py` | Auditor project-wide: `.py` de implementación que no son target de ningún contrato (código fuera del flujo gate); exime d","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#102","metadata":{"content":"n contrato (código fuera del flujo gate); exime datos puros | no |\n| `runners/audit_annotations.py` | Auditor project-wide: nombres en anotaciones sin importar/definir; caza bugs de portabilidad que lazy annotations (PEP 649) enmascara | no |\n| `runners/mutation_audit.py` | Mide la fuerza del oráculo vía mutation testing determinista (mutaciones fijas → corre los tests congelados por mutante); superviviente = test débil | no |\n| `runners/approve_tests.py` | Firma humana de los tests (`tests_sha256`), a prueba de manipulación | no |\n| `runners/orchestrator.py` | Loop **stateless**: pequeño implementa → tests fallan/complejidad falla → reintenta (sin memoria) → escala al grande | sí (worker) |\n| `runners/test_audit.py` | Auditoría *advisory* de los tests contra el contrato |","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#103","metadata":{"content":"ría *advisory* de los tests contra el contrato | sí (advisory) |\n| `runners/measure.py` | Harness de medición: tokens/intentos/escalados, costo vs loop grande | no |\n| `runners/complexity_mcp.py` | Servidor MCP (stdio JSON-RPC) que expone el sustrato | no |\n| `runners/mcp_smoke.py` | Smoke test del MCP | no |\n| `runners/guardrails_lang.yaml` | Guardrails específicos por lenguaje | no |\n| `runners/eval_gate.py` | **Pilar de evals — Tier 1**: veredicto determinista sobre output NO determinista (agentes).","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#104","metadata":{"content":"erminista sobre output NO determinista (agentes).","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#105","metadata":{"content":"rminista sobre output NO determinista (agentes).","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#106","metadata":{"content":"minista sobre output NO determinista (agentes).","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#107","metadata":{"content":"inista sobre output NO determinista (agentes).","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#108","metadata":{"content":"nista sobre output NO determinista (agentes).","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#109","metadata":{"content":"ista sobre output NO determinista (agentes).","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#11","metadata":{"content":"ue no se puede engañar.\n\n## Qué hay acá","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#110","metadata":{"content":"sta sobre output NO determinista (agentes).","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#111","metadata":{"content":"ta sobre output NO determinista (agentes).","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#112","metadata":{"content":"a sobre output NO determinista (agentes).","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#113","metadata":{"content":"sobre output NO determinista (agentes).","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#114","metadata":{"content":"sobre output NO determinista (agentes).","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#115","metadata":{"content":"obre output NO determinista (agentes).","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#116","metadata":{"content":"bre output NO determinista (agentes).","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#117","metadata":{"content":"re output NO determinista (agentes).","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#118","metadata":{"content":"e output NO determinista (agentes).","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#119","metadata":{"content":"output NO determinista (agentes).","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#12","metadata":{"content":"e no se puede engañar.\n\n## Qué hay acá","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#120","metadata":{"content":"output NO determinista (agentes).","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#121","metadata":{"content":"utput NO determinista (agentes).","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#122","metadata":{"content":"tput NO determinista (agentes).","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#123","metadata":{"content":"put NO determinista (agentes).","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#124","metadata":{"content":"ut NO determinista (agentes).","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#125","metadata":{"content":"t NO determinista (agentes).","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#126","metadata":{"content":"NO determinista (agentes).","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#127","metadata":{"content":"NO determinista (agentes).","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#128","metadata":{"content":"O determinista (agentes).","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#129","metadata":{"content":"determinista (agentes).","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#13","metadata":{"content":"no se puede engañar.\n\n## Qué hay acá","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#130","metadata":{"content":"determinista (agentes).","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#131","metadata":{"content":"eterminista (agentes).","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#132","metadata":{"content":"terminista (agentes).","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#133","metadata":{"content":"erminista (agentes).","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#134","metadata":{"content":"rminista (agentes).","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#135","metadata":{"content":"minista (agentes).","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#136","metadata":{"content":"inista (agentes).","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#137","metadata":{"content":"nista (agentes).","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#138","metadata":{"content":"ista (agentes).","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#139","metadata":{"content":"sta (agentes).","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#14","metadata":{"content":"no se puede engañar.\n\n## Qué hay acá","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#140","metadata":{"content":"ta (agentes).","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#141","metadata":{"content":"a (agentes).","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#142","metadata":{"content":"(agentes).","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#143","metadata":{"content":"(agentes).","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#144","metadata":{"content":"agentes).","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#145","metadata":{"content":"gentes).","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#146","metadata":{"content":"entes).","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#147","metadata":{"content":"ntes).","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#148","metadata":{"content":"tes).","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#149","metadata":{"content":"es).","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#15","metadata":{"content":"o se puede engañar.\n\n## Qué hay acá","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#150","metadata":{"content":"s).","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#151","metadata":{"content":").","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#152","metadata":{"content":".","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#153","metadata":{"content":"Dataset congelado + checks (schema, contención, citas/groundedness, PII, trayectoria) | no |\n| `runners/eval_checks.py` | Checkers deterministas Tier 1 (una función por check; anti-alucinación de fuentes y evaluación de trayectoria) | no |\n| `runners/approve_eval_cases.py` | Firma humana del dataset de evals (`cases_sha256`), a prueba de manipulación | no |\n| `runners/eval_judge.py` | **Tier 2 (opt-in)**: juez LLM acotado (modelo pinneado, temp 0) — el único módulo del pilar que llama a un LLM | sí (opt-in) |\n| `runners/judge_audit.py` | Fuerza/deriva del juez: acuerdo vs golden set humano (análogo a `mutation_audit`); si baja del umbral, falla el JUEZ | sí (opt-in) |\n| `contracts/` | Rubrics firmados: `pre-complexity-agent`, `complexity-agent`, `task-author-agent`, `eval-agen","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#154","metadata":{"content":"complexity-agent`, `task-author-agent`, `eval-agent` (juez Tier 2) | — |\n\n## Quickstart\n\n```bash\npip install -r requirements.txt\n\n# 1) Gate determinista sobre un task-contract de ejemplo (PASS)\npython runners/task_gate.py examples/sandbox/task.md\n\n# 2) Tests congelados (deterministas, sin LLM): gate + gobernanza L2 (Ed25519) + reglas tc_lint\npython -m unittest tests.test_gates tests.test_l2_governance tests.test_tc_lint_rules -v\n\n# 3) Linter de un task-contract\npython runners/tc_lint.py examples/sandbox/task.md\n```\n\n### Como hook de auto-validación en Claude Code\n\n`settings.json` → `hooks.PostToolUse` con matcher `Write|Edit`:\n\n```json\n{ \"command\": \"python runners/complexity_gate.py\" }\n```","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#155","metadata":{"content":"mand\": \"python runners/complexity_gate.py\" }\n```\n\nCada archivo que el agente escribe se mide con el backend de su lenguaje (por extensión, o\n`--language` en CLI); si una métrica entra en CRÍTICA (umbral firmado), el hook bloquea y pide\nrefactor. Determinista, sin tokens. Una extensión sin backend registrado es un **no-op anunciado**\n(aviso por stderr, exit 0), nunca un fallo silencioso. Python siempre; el resto de lenguajes\nrequiere la dep opcional tree-sitter (ver «Conformancia multi-lenguaje»).\n\n### Instalación como paquete (console scripts)\n\nPara usar ccdd-gate sin clonar ni rutas absolutas, instálalo como distribución (deja los scripts\n`ccdd-mcp`, `ccdd-lint`, `ccdd-gate`, `ccdd-measure` en el PATH):","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#156","metadata":{"content":"-lint`, `ccdd-gate`, `ccdd-measure` en el PATH):\n\n```bash\npipx install ccdd-gate        # o: uvx ccdd-gate · o: pip install ccdd-gate\n```\n\n> El **modo desde el repo** (`python runners/<x>.py`) sigue funcionando para desarrollo.\n> Nota: los datos de gobernanza (rubric/attestations bajo `contracts/`, schema en la raíz) se\n> resuelven en el layout del repo / instalación editable (`pip install -e .`); el núcleo\n> determinista (medir/lintar/gate/MCP) funciona en cualquier modo.\n\n### Como MCP\n\nCon el paquete instalado, el `.mcp.json` no necesita clonar el repo ni `cwd`:\n\n```json\n{ \"mcpServers\": { \"ccdd\": { \"command\": \"ccdd-mcp\" } } }\n```\n\nDesde el repo, copiá `.mcp.json.example` a `.mcp.json`. Tools (sin LLM):","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#157","metadata":{"content":"cp.json.example` a `.mcp.json`. Tools (sin LLM):","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#158","metadata":{"content":"p.json.example` a `.mcp.json`. Tools (sin LLM):","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#159","metadata":{"content":".json.example` a `.mcp.json`. Tools (sin LLM):","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#16","metadata":{"content":"se puede engañar.\n\n## Qué hay acá","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#160","metadata":{"content":"json.example` a `.mcp.json`. Tools (sin LLM):","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#161","metadata":{"content":"son.example` a `.mcp.json`. Tools (sin LLM):","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#162","metadata":{"content":"on.example` a `.mcp.json`. Tools (sin LLM):","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#163","metadata":{"content":"n.example` a `.mcp.json`. Tools (sin LLM):","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#164","metadata":{"content":".example` a `.mcp.json`. Tools (sin LLM):","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#165","metadata":{"content":"example` a `.mcp.json`. Tools (sin LLM):","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#166","metadata":{"content":"xample` a `.mcp.json`. Tools (sin LLM):","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#167","metadata":{"content":"ample` a `.mcp.json`. Tools (sin LLM):","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#168","metadata":{"content":"mple` a `.mcp.json`. Tools (sin LLM):","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#169","metadata":{"content":"ple` a `.mcp.json`. Tools (sin LLM):","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#17","metadata":{"content":"se puede engañar.\n\n## Qué hay acá","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#170","metadata":{"content":"le` a `.mcp.json`. Tools (sin LLM):","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#171","metadata":{"content":"e` a `.mcp.json`. Tools (sin LLM):","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#172","metadata":{"content":"` a `.mcp.json`. Tools (sin LLM):","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#173","metadata":{"content":"a `.mcp.json`. Tools (sin LLM):","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#174","metadata":{"content":"a `.mcp.json`. Tools (sin LLM):","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#175","metadata":{"content":"`.mcp.json`. Tools (sin LLM):","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#176","metadata":{"content":"`.mcp.json`. Tools (sin LLM):","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#177","metadata":{"content":".mcp.json`. Tools (sin LLM):","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#178","metadata":{"content":"mcp.json`. Tools (sin LLM):","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#179","metadata":{"content":"cp.json`. Tools (sin LLM):","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#18","metadata":{"content":"e puede engañar.\n\n## Qué hay acá","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#180","metadata":{"content":"p.json`. Tools (sin LLM):","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#181","metadata":{"content":".json`. Tools (sin LLM):","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#182","metadata":{"content":"json`. Tools (sin LLM):","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#183","metadata":{"content":"son`. Tools (sin LLM):","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#184","metadata":{"content":"on`. Tools (sin LLM):","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#185","metadata":{"content":"n`. Tools (sin LLM):","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#186","metadata":{"content":"`. Tools (sin LLM):","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#187","metadata":{"content":". Tools (sin LLM):","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#188","metadata":{"content":"Tools (sin LLM):","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#189","metadata":{"content":"Tools (sin LLM):","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#19","metadata":{"content":"puede engañar.\n\n## Qué hay acá","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#190","metadata":{"content":"ools (sin LLM):","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#191","metadata":{"content":"ols (sin LLM):","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#192","metadata":{"content":"ls (sin LLM):","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#193","metadata":{"content":"s (sin LLM):","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#194","metadata":{"content":"(sin LLM):","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#195","metadata":{"content":"(sin LLM):","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#196","metadata":{"content":"sin LLM):","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#197","metadata":{"content":"in LLM):","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#198","metadata":{"content":"n LLM):","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#199","metadata":{"content":"LLM):","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#2","metadata":{"content":"rida.\n\nEl mismo principio cubre **dos pilares**:\n\n- **Código** (gate de complejidad/tests): verifica que la función implementada respeta el budget\n  y pasa los property-tests congelados. 100% determinista.\n- **Comportamiento de agentes** (pilar de evals): para la salida NO determinista de un agente\n  (texto/JSON), un dataset congelado + checks deterministas (schema, contención, citas/groundedness\n  anti-alucinación, PII, trayectoria) deciden PASS/FAIL sin LLM (**Tier 1**); un juez LLM acotado y\n  auditado contra un golden set es **Tier 2 opt-in**. Ver [Pilar de evals](#pilar-de-evals-gatear-output-no-determinista-tier-1--tier-2-opt-in).","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#20","metadata":{"content":"puede engañar.\n\n## Qué hay acá","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#200","metadata":{"content":"LLM):","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#201","metadata":{"content":"LM):","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#202","metadata":{"content":"M):","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#203","metadata":{"content":"):","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#204","metadata":{"content":":","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#205","metadata":{"content":"- `measure_complexity(code)` — métricas AST reales por función.\n- `complexity_rubric(agent)` — el criterio gobernado (system/policies/thresholds) firmado.\n- `scan_guardrails(code, agent?, language?, filename?)` — guardrails deterministas: secretos (texto-puro,\n  igual en todo lenguaje), anidamiento (estructural, vía el backend del lenguaje), `dsv_check` (anti-alucinación por \"drift\", exige coincidencia exacta con HEAD local) y específicos por\n  lenguaje opt-in (`runners/guardrails_lang.yaml`, p. ej. `no-eval`). `agent` evalúa contra ese contrato.","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#206","metadata":{"content":"`no-eval`). `agent` evalúa contra ese contrato. Sin `language`, Python.\n- `lint_task_contract(contract_text, test_code?)` - valida un task-contract (anti-desvarío del modelo grande).\n- `scan_dependencies(code, deps_allowed?, local_roots?)` - imports top-level de terceros NO permitidos (enforcement de `deps_allowed` / anti-slopsquatting). Determinista, sin LLM. `local_roots` (lista de dirs, opcional) exime los imports que resuelvan a un módulo/paquete local bajo alguno de esos roots (mismo mecanismo que el gate 4); sin el campo, ningún módulo local se exime.\n- `check_signature(source, fn_name, expected_signature, language?)` - \"\" si la firma implementada coincide con la esperada (nombre + nombres de params en orden), o el desajuste.","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#207","metadata":{"content":"re + nombres de params en orden), o el desajuste. Python usa AST nativo; otros lenguajes usan tree-sitter si la gramática está disponible (TS/TSX/JS/Rust/Go/Java/C#/PHP/Ruby/Kotlin/C/Swift/C++; Kotlin y C degradan a aridad genérica en la firma, ver \"Conformancia multi-lenguaje\"). Default language: python. Determinista, sin LLM.\n- `check_purity(source, fn_name, target_line?)` - operaciones impuras del cuerpo (`gate-purity`). Sin LLM.\n- `check_mutable_defaults(source, fn_name, target_line?)` - params con default mutable (`gate-mutdef`). Sin LLM.\n- `check_bare_except(source, fn_name, target_line?)` - líneas de `except:` desnudo (`gate-bareexcept`). Sin LLM.\n- `check_asserts(source, fn_name, target_line?)` - líneas de `assert` (`gate-assert`).","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#208","metadata":{"content":"et_line?)` - líneas de `assert` (`gate-assert`). Sin LLM.\n- `check_none_cmp(source, fn_name, target_line?)` - comparaciones con None por ==/!= (`gate-nonecmp`). Sin LLM.\n- `run_rules_gate(rules_path?, root?)` - aplica los checks deterministas **project-wide por glob** desde un `rules.yaml`. Sin LLM.\n- `run_linter_gate(linters_path?, root?)` - envuelve **linters externos deterministas** como checks opt-in desde un `linters.yaml` (lista de `{tool, version, files?, args?, required?}`); version pineada, sin LLM. Hoy solo adaptador `ruff` (dep opcional, no del paquete).\n- `run_integration_gate(task_path)` - **veredicto PASS/FAIL unificado** de un contrato YA EN DISCO (lint + aprobación de tests + tests congelados + complejidad ≤ budget), idéntico a la CLI `task_gate.py`.","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#209","metadata":{"content":"d ≤ budget), idéntico a la CLI `task_gate.py`. Para `kind:group` compone las hijas + el test de integración sobre los archivos reales (sin sandbox). El agente NO implementa: delega a `run_ephemeral_agent`.\n- `run_ephemeral_agent(task_path)` - delega la **implementación** al modelo pequeño local y la valida contra el gate. El **servidor** fija modelo y endpoint; el LLM anfitrión solo pasa `task_path` (no elige el modelo). El **operador** puede elegir el modelo por entorno (`CCDD_EXECUTOR_MODEL`, `CCDD_EXECUTOR_API`) sin tocar la fuente; el LLM no.","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#21","metadata":{"content":"uede engañar.\n\n## Qué hay acá","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#210","metadata":{"content":"DD_EXECUTOR_API`) sin tocar la fuente; el LLM no. Default: `qwen3-coder:480b-cloud` vía Ollama (`http://localhost:11434/v1`).\n- `audit_composition(root?)` - composición sin gatear project-wide; separa deuda de FORMA (composición ejercitada por el test del composer) de deuda de COMPORTAMIENTO (mock o test ausente). `ok` = sin deuda de comportamiento.\n- `audit_orphan_targets(root?)` - `.py` de implementación que no son target de ningún contrato (exime tests/`__init__`/datos puros).","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#211","metadata":{"content":"ún contrato (exime tests/`__init__`/datos puros). Para proyectos 100% CCDD.\n- `audit_annotations(root?)` - nombres usados en anotaciones sin importar/definir, sobre todos los targets; caza bugs de portabilidad que Python 3.14 (lazy annotations) enmascara en runtime.\n- `mutation_audit(task_path)` - fuerza del oráculo vía mutation testing determinista; un mutante sobreviviente delata un test débil. Opt-in (corre los tests por mutante).\n- `request_human_attestation(code, reason)` - permite al agente pedir una excepción firmada cuando no puede reducir la complejidad por reglas de negocio.\n- `run_eval_gate(eval_path)` - **pilar de evals (Tier 1)**: veredicto determinista sobre el output NO determinista de un agente (dataset congelado + checks).","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#212","metadata":{"content":"inista de un agente (dataset congelado + checks). Sin LLM.\n- `eval_rubric()` - rúbrica firmada del juez Tier 2 (contrato `eval-agent`).\n- `judge_audit(eval_path, provider?)` - acuerdo del juez Tier 2 vs golden set humano; si baja del umbral, el juez no es de fiar. Provider `stub` (determinista) por defecto.\n\n**Checklist de cierre** (antes de dar una tarea por terminada): corré las cuatro auditorías —`audit_composition`, `audit_orphan_targets`, `audit_annotations` y `mutation_audit`— hasta `ok:true`. El gate de función no cubre composición, código huérfano, anotaciones ni la fuerza del oráculo; quedarse con la auditoría que da verde y declarar \"todo en verde\" es el modo de falla que la checklist existe para cerrar (y que el CI hace no-opcional).","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#213","metadata":{"content":"iste para cerrar (y que el CI hace no-opcional).\n\n## Pilar de evals: gatear output NO determinista (Tier 1 + Tier 2 opt-in)\n\nEl gate de complejidad/tests verifica **código** (funciones con oráculo independiente). Pero un\nagente de producción (un bot de soporte, un asistente de research) produce **texto/JSON no\ndeterminista** que ese gate no cubre. El pilar de evals lo cierra **sin renunciar al determinismo\ndonde se puede**, en dos niveles:","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#214","metadata":{"content":"l determinismo\ndonde se puede**, en dos niveles:\n\n- **Tier 1 — checks deterministas, sin LLM** (`eval_gate.py` + `eval_checks.py`). Sobre cada caso\n  de un dataset CONGELADO y firmado (`cases_sha256`, igual que `tests_sha256`): schema del output,\n  contención/ausencia de términos, `must_cite` + **groundedness** (toda cita apunta a una fuente\n  existente → anti-alucinación), PII, y **evaluación de trayectoria** (tools requeridas/prohibidas,\n  `max_steps`). Veredicto = función del budget: `pass_rate ≥ pass_rate_min` y violaciones duras\n  ≤ `forbidden_violations_max`. **Mismo input → mismo veredicto.** Muchos agentes (extracción,\n  clasificación, routing) se gatean 100% aquí.","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#215","metadata":{"content":"clasificación, routing) se gatean 100% aquí.\n\n- **Tier 2 — juez LLM ACOTADO, opt-in** (`eval_judge.py` + `judge_audit.py`). Solo para lo\n  genuinamente subjetivo (coherencia, utilidad). El modelo se pinnea (`temperature 0`) y su\n  veredicto **no cuenta hasta pasar `judge_audit`**: el juez se calibra contra un golden set\n  atestado por humano y debe alcanzar `agreement ≥ agreement_min`. Es a la calidad lo que\n  `mutation_audit` es al oráculo: no confía en el juez, lo mide. La única relajación de\n  determinismo (el score por-corrida del LLM) queda acotada y auditada; cualquier deriva del modelo\n  pinneado la caza `judge_audit` en CI.\n\n```bash\n# Firmar el dataset (OK humano, congela los casos)\npython runners/approve_eval_cases.py examples/eval/support-bot-refunds/eval.md","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#216","metadata":{"content":"ses.py examples/eval/support-bot-refunds/eval.md\n\n# Veredicto Tier 1 (sin LLM, reproducible)\npython runners/eval_gate.py examples/eval/support-bot-refunds/eval.md\n\n# Calibrar el juez Tier 2 contra el golden set (offline con provider stub)\npython runners/judge_audit.py examples/eval/support-bot-refunds/eval.md\n```\n\nEl **eval-contract** (front-matter YAML + cuerpo, espeja al task-contract) declara `target`,\n`agent_entry`, `dataset`, `budget`, `deterministic_checks` y el bloque `judge` (opt-in). Ver\n`examples/eval/support-bot-refunds/` para el ejemplo end-to-end (agente determinista de juguete,\ndataset firmado, schema y rúbrica).\n\n## El loop grande/pequeño (Stateless Feedback y Evolución CEFL)","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#217","metadata":{"content":"/pequeño (Stateless Feedback y Evolución CEFL)\n\nEl loop es **stateless** (sin estado) pero incorpora mecánicas evolutivas inspiradas en CEFL (Candidate Expansion and Freezing):","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#218","metadata":{"content":"adas en CEFL (Candidate Expansion and Freezing):","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#219","metadata":{"content":"das en CEFL (Candidate Expansion and Freezing):","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#22","metadata":{"content":"ede engañar.\n\n## Qué hay acá","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#220","metadata":{"content":"as en CEFL (Candidate Expansion and Freezing):","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#221","metadata":{"content":"s en CEFL (Candidate Expansion and Freezing):","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#222","metadata":{"content":"en CEFL (Candidate Expansion and Freezing):","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#223","metadata":{"content":"en CEFL (Candidate Expansion and Freezing):","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#224","metadata":{"content":"n CEFL (Candidate Expansion and Freezing):","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#225","metadata":{"content":"CEFL (Candidate Expansion and Freezing):","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#226","metadata":{"content":"CEFL (Candidate Expansion and Freezing):","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#227","metadata":{"content":"EFL (Candidate Expansion and Freezing):","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#228","metadata":{"content":"FL (Candidate Expansion and Freezing):","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#229","metadata":{"content":"L (Candidate Expansion and Freezing):","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#23","metadata":{"content":"de engañar.\n\n## Qué hay acá","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#230","metadata":{"content":"(Candidate Expansion and Freezing):","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#231","metadata":{"content":"(Candidate Expansion and Freezing):","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#232","metadata":{"content":"Candidate Expansion and Freezing):","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#233","metadata":{"content":"andidate Expansion and Freezing):","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#234","metadata":{"content":"ndidate Expansion and Freezing):","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#235","metadata":{"content":"didate Expansion and Freezing):","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#236","metadata":{"content":"idate Expansion and Freezing):","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#237","metadata":{"content":"date Expansion and Freezing):","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#238","metadata":{"content":"ate Expansion and Freezing):","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#239","metadata":{"content":"te Expansion and Freezing):","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#24","metadata":{"content":"e engañar.\n\n## Qué hay acá","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#240","metadata":{"content":"e Expansion and Freezing):","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#241","metadata":{"content":"Expansion and Freezing):","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#242","metadata":{"content":"Expansion and Freezing):","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#243","metadata":{"content":"xpansion and Freezing):","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#244","metadata":{"content":"pansion and Freezing):","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#245","metadata":{"content":"ansion and Freezing):","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#246","metadata":{"content":"nsion and Freezing):","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#247","metadata":{"content":"sion and Freezing):","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#248","metadata":{"content":"ion and Freezing):","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#249","metadata":{"content":"on and Freezing):","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#25","metadata":{"content":"engañar.\n\n## Qué hay acá","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#250","metadata":{"content":"n and Freezing):","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#251","metadata":{"content":"and Freezing):","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#252","metadata":{"content":"and Freezing):","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#253","metadata":{"content":"nd Freezing):","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#254","metadata":{"content":"d Freezing):","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#255","metadata":{"content":"Freezing):","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#256","metadata":{"content":"Freezing):","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#257","metadata":{"content":"reezing):\n\n1. **Expansión Paralela:** El orquestador no pide 1 intento; pide N candidatos paralelos (`--candidates 3`).\n2. **Torneo de Complejidad (Freezing):** Cada candidato se aísla y se valida contra los tests y el budget de complejidad. Si varios pasan, el Gate elige automáticamente **el que tenga la menor puntuación matemática de complejidad**, congelándolo como la respuesta definitiva.\n3. **Feedback Masivo (Partial Success):** Si todos los candidatos fallan, el sistema no reenvía código roto uno por uno. Agrupa las N soluciones fallidas junto a sus errores (stack traces) en un JSON combinado masivo. Esto permite al modelo en la siguiente iteración aprender cruzando los fracasos de todas sus rutas exploratorias, resolviendo problemas que un solo reintento jamás lograría.","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#258","metadata":{"content":"roblemas que un solo reintento jamás lograría.\n\n```bash\n# OFFLINE (sin modelo): stub que entrega 1 impl rota y 1 buena -> intento 1 FAIL, intento 2 PASS\npython runners/orchestrator.py examples/sandbox/loop_demo/task.md \\\n  --provider stub \\\n  --stub examples/sandbox/loop_demo/_stub_bad.py \\\n  --stub examples/sandbox/loop_demo/_stub_good.py --max-attempts 3\n\n# CON MODELOS: el pequeño genera 3 vías paralelas; si todas fallan, escala al grande\npython runners/orchestrator.py examples/sandbox/loop_demo/task.md \\\n  --provider openai --model <modelo-chico> --candidates 3 \\\n  --escalate-provider ollama --escalate-model <modelo-grande> --escalate-attempts 2\n```","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#259","metadata":{"content":"-model <modelo-grande> --escalate-attempts 2\n```\n\nProviders: `ollama`, `openai` (LM Studio/vLLM, urllib stdlib), `anthropic` (SDK), y `stub`\n(secuencia offline para probar la mecánica sin modelo).\n\n## task-contract (formato)\n\nFront-matter YAML (machine-checkable) + cuerpo Markdown (prescriptivo). Ver\n`examples/sandbox/task.md` y el rubric de autoría en `contracts/task-author-agent/`.\nRegla central: **especifica el contrato y los property-tests con oráculo independiente,\nNO el algoritmo**. Los tests se congelan y firman *antes* de que el implementador toque la tarea.","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#26","metadata":{"content":"engañar.\n\n## Qué hay acá","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#260","metadata":{"content":"*antes* de que el implementador toque la tarea.\n\n**Campo `target_line` (opcional, desambiguación).** El gate de complejidad resuelve la función\nobjetivo por nombre. Si el target tiene **varias funciones/métodos homónimos** (p. ej. `set` en\nvarias clases), declara `target_line: N` (la línea de la def correcta) para que mida esa y no otra.\nSin desambiguador y con >1 def del nombre, el gate devuelve **INVALID** (ambiguo) en vez de medir la\núltima en silencio (issue #41). Con un solo match el campo es innecesario (comportamiento idéntico).","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#261","metadata":{"content":"campo es innecesario (comportamiento idéntico).","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#262","metadata":{"content":"ampo es innecesario (comportamiento idéntico).","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#263","metadata":{"content":"mpo es innecesario (comportamiento idéntico).","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#264","metadata":{"content":"po es innecesario (comportamiento idéntico).","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#265","metadata":{"content":"o es innecesario (comportamiento idéntico).","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#266","metadata":{"content":"es innecesario (comportamiento idéntico).","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#267","metadata":{"content":"es innecesario (comportamiento idéntico).","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#268","metadata":{"content":"s innecesario (comportamiento idéntico).","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#269","metadata":{"content":"innecesario (comportamiento idéntico).","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#27","metadata":{"content":"ngañar.\n\n## Qué hay acá","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#270","metadata":{"content":"innecesario (comportamiento idéntico).","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#271","metadata":{"content":"nnecesario (comportamiento idéntico).","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#272","metadata":{"content":"necesario (comportamiento idéntico).","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#273","metadata":{"content":"ecesario (comportamiento idéntico).","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#274","metadata":{"content":"cesario (comportamiento idéntico).","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#275","metadata":{"content":"esario (comportamiento idéntico).","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#276","metadata":{"content":"sario (comportamiento idéntico).","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#277","metadata":{"content":"ario (comportamiento idéntico).","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#278","metadata":{"content":"rio (comportamiento idéntico).","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#279","metadata":{"content":"io (comportamiento idéntico).","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#28","metadata":{"content":"gañar.\n\n## Qué hay acá","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#280","metadata":{"content":"o (comportamiento idéntico).","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#281","metadata":{"content":"(comportamiento idéntico).","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#282","metadata":{"content":"(comportamiento idéntico).","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#283","metadata":{"content":"comportamiento idéntico).","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#284","metadata":{"content":"omportamiento idéntico).","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#285","metadata":{"content":"mportamiento idéntico).","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#286","metadata":{"content":"portamiento idéntico).","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#287","metadata":{"content":"ortamiento idéntico).","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#288","metadata":{"content":"rtamiento idéntico).","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#289","metadata":{"content":"tamiento idéntico).","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#29","metadata":{"content":"añar.\n\n## Qué hay acá","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#290","metadata":{"content":"amiento idéntico).","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#291","metadata":{"content":"miento idéntico).","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#292","metadata":{"content":"iento idéntico).","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#293","metadata":{"content":"ento idéntico).","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#294","metadata":{"content":"nto idéntico).","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#295","metadata":{"content":"to idéntico).","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#296","metadata":{"content":"o idéntico).","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#297","metadata":{"content":"idéntico).","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#298","metadata":{"content":"idéntico).","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#299","metadata":{"content":"déntico).","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#3","metadata":{"content":"r-output-no-determinista-tier-1--tier-2-opt-in).\n\n> Construido sobre [CCDD](https://github.com/MauricioPerera/ccdd) (incluido aquí como\n> `ccdd.py`, MIT). El sustrato determinista no llama a ningún LLM: el cerebro es el agente\n> anfitrión (Claude Code, Cursor, etc.) que invoca estas herramientas.\n\n## Instalación (PyPI)\n\n`ccdd-gate` está publicado en [PyPI](https://pypi.org/project/ccdd-gate/) — esta es la vía\nrecomendada para usuarios (sin clonar, sin rutas absolutas):\n\n```bash\npip install ccdd-gate\n# o: pipx install ccdd-gate · uvx ccdd-gate\n```\n\nQuedan disponibles los CLIs `ccdd-lint`, `ccdd-gate`, `ccdd-measure` y el servidor MCP\n`ccdd-mcp` (todos en el PATH).\n\n### Registrar el MCP en un cliente (Claude Code / Desktop)","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#30","metadata":{"content":"ñar.\n\n## Qué hay acá","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#300","metadata":{"content":"éntico).","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#301","metadata":{"content":"ntico).","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#302","metadata":{"content":"tico).","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#303","metadata":{"content":"ico).","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#304","metadata":{"content":"co).","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#305","metadata":{"content":"o).","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#306","metadata":{"content":").","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#307","metadata":{"content":".","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#308","metadata":{"content":"**Campo `enforce_deps` (opcional, anti-slopsquatting).** Si `enforce_deps: true`, el gate corre la\netapa **gate-deps**: flaggea los imports top-level del target que no estén en `deps_allowed` (ni en\nla stdlib) y falla con `stage: gate-deps`. **Opt-in** (default off): los contratos que no lo declaran\nno cambian. Los módulos **locales del propio proyecto** se eximen automáticamente: el gate pasa como\nraíces de búsqueda locales el directorio del contrato y el del target, así que un import top-level que\nresuelva a `<dir>/m.py` o `<dir>/m/__init__.py` bajo alguno de esos dirs no se flaggea (no hace falta\nlistarlo en `deps_allowed`).","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#309","metadata":{"content":"aggea (no hace falta\nlistarlo en `deps_allowed`). Los imports de tercero no listados siguen flaggeándose normalmente.\nLimitación actual: la exención solo mira el top-level de esos dos dirs (no recursiva ni configurable a\notros dirs del repo); y sigue siendo solo Python.\n\n**Conformidad de firma (etapa gate-signature, default-on).** El gate compara la firma IMPLEMENTADA\ncon la `signature` del contrato (nombre + nombres de parámetros en orden; ignora anotaciones,\ndefaults y retorno) y falla con `stage: gate-signature` si difieren — caza el drift de firma que\nrompe a los callers. Es **default-on**: no requiere campo. Solo Python (compara vía AST).","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#31","metadata":{"content":"ar.\n\n## Qué hay acá","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#310","metadata":{"content":"requiere campo. Solo Python (compara vía AST).\n\n**Gates de antipatrones opt-in (default-off, Python, vía AST).** Cada uno corre solo si el contrato\ndeclara su campo; sin él, el contrato no cambia. Todos fallan con su propio `stage`:","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#311","metadata":{"content":"o no cambia. Todos fallan con su propio `stage`:\n\n| Campo | Etapa | Falla si la función… |\n|---|---|---|\n| `pure: true` | `gate-purity` | tiene operaciones impuras (print/open/eval/exec/`__import__`/input, global/nonlocal, import interno) |\n| `forbid_mutable_defaults: true` | `gate-mutdef` | tiene params con default mutable (`[]`/`{}`/`set()`/`list()`/`dict()`) |\n| `forbid_bare_except: true` | `gate-bareexcept` | tiene un `except:` desnudo (sin tipo) |\n| `forbid_assert: true` | `gate-assert` | usa `assert` (desaparece con `python -O`) |\n| `forbid_none_eq: true` | `gate-nonecmp` | compara con None usando `==`/`!=` en vez de `is`/`is not` |","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#312","metadata":{"content":"None usando `==`/`!=` en vez de `is`/`is not` |\n\nCada uno honra `target_line` para funciones homónimas y tiene su tool MCP (`check_purity`,\n`check_mutable_defaults`, `check_bare_except`, `check_asserts`, `check_none_cmp`).","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#313","metadata":{"content":"are_except`, `check_asserts`, `check_none_cmp`).\n\n**Reglas project-wide por glob (`rules_gate`).** Los gates de antipatrón de arriba se disparan\n**por contrato**. Para aplicarlos a TODO el repo sin contratos, `runners/rules_gate.py` lee un\n`rules.yaml` declarativo (lista de `{check, files}`) y corre el check determinista sobre cada función\nde los archivos que matchean el glob — política de repo, no solo por función gateada. La idea del\nformato declarativo + glob está tomada de [autorules](https://github.com/markwylde/autorules), pero\nel **árbitro es AST determinista, no un LLM** (autorules usa un juez LLM; ccdd-gate no). Ver\n`examples/rules.yaml.example` y la evaluación completa en\n[`docs/evaluations/autorules.md`](docs/evaluations/autorules.md).","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#314","metadata":{"content":"s/autorules.md`](docs/evaluations/autorules.md).\n\n```bash\npython runners/rules_gate.py rules.yaml [root]   # exit 0 ok · 1 violaciones · 2 config inválida\n```","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#315","metadata":{"content":"0 ok · 1 violaciones · 2 config inválida\n```","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#316","metadata":{"content":"0 ok · 1 violaciones · 2 config inválida\n```","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#317","metadata":{"content":"ok · 1 violaciones · 2 config inválida\n```","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#318","metadata":{"content":"ok · 1 violaciones · 2 config inválida\n```","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#319","metadata":{"content":"k · 1 violaciones · 2 config inválida\n```","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#32","metadata":{"content":"r.\n\n## Qué hay acá","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#320","metadata":{"content":"· 1 violaciones · 2 config inválida\n```","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#321","metadata":{"content":"· 1 violaciones · 2 config inválida\n```","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#322","metadata":{"content":"1 violaciones · 2 config inválida\n```","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#323","metadata":{"content":"1 violaciones · 2 config inválida\n```","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#324","metadata":{"content":"violaciones · 2 config inválida\n```","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#325","metadata":{"content":"violaciones · 2 config inválida\n```","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#326","metadata":{"content":"iolaciones · 2 config inválida\n```","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#327","metadata":{"content":"olaciones · 2 config inválida\n```","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#328","metadata":{"content":"laciones · 2 config inválida\n```","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#329","metadata":{"content":"aciones · 2 config inválida\n```","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#33","metadata":{"content":".\n\n## Qué hay acá","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#330","metadata":{"content":"ciones · 2 config inválida\n```","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#331","metadata":{"content":"iones · 2 config inválida\n```","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#332","metadata":{"content":"ones · 2 config inválida\n```","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#333","metadata":{"content":"nes · 2 config inválida\n```","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#334","metadata":{"content":"es · 2 config inválida\n```","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#335","metadata":{"content":"s · 2 config inválida\n```","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#336","metadata":{"content":"· 2 config inválida\n```","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#337","metadata":{"content":"· 2 config inválida\n```","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#338","metadata":{"content":"2 config inválida\n```","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#339","metadata":{"content":"2 config inválida\n```","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#34","metadata":{"content":"## Qué hay acá","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#340","metadata":{"content":"config inválida\n```","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#341","metadata":{"content":"config inválida\n```","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#342","metadata":{"content":"onfig inválida\n```","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#343","metadata":{"content":"nfig inválida\n```","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#344","metadata":{"content":"fig inválida\n```","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#345","metadata":{"content":"ig inválida\n```","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#346","metadata":{"content":"g inválida\n```","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#347","metadata":{"content":"inválida\n```","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#348","metadata":{"content":"inválida\n```","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#349","metadata":{"content":"nválida\n```","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#35","metadata":{"content":"## Qué hay acá","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#350","metadata":{"content":"válida\n```","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#351","metadata":{"content":"álida\n```","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#352","metadata":{"content":"lida\n```","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#353","metadata":{"content":"ida\n```","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#354","metadata":{"content":"da\n```","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#355","metadata":{"content":"a\n```","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#356","metadata":{"content":"```","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#357","metadata":{"content":"```","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#358","metadata":{"content":"``","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#359","metadata":{"content":"`","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#36","metadata":{"content":"## Qué hay acá","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#360","metadata":{"content":"**Linters externos deterministas (`linter_gate`).** Hermano de `rules_gate` pero el veredicto lo emite un\n**linter externo** invocado como subproceso con salida machine-readable, no un AST propio: el gate no\nreimplementa reglas, delega en la herramienta y solo normaliza su salida a `findings`. **Opt-in** desde un\n`linters.yaml` declarativo (lista de `{tool, version, files?, args?, required?}`). La salida de un linter\ndepende de su versión, por eso `version` es **pin exacto obligatorio**: versión instalada != pin → entorno\ninválido (exit 2, **no es PASS**). Tool ausente + `required:false` → skip anunciado + exit 0 (precedente\ntree-sitter del repo); `required:true` → exit 2. Findings → exit 1; limpio → exit 0.","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#361","metadata":{"content":"→ exit 2. Findings → exit 1; limpio → exit 0. **HOY solo hay\nadaptador `ruff`** (el registro queda listo para clippy/eslint/golangci-lint sin implementarlos); **`ruff`\nNO es dependencia del paquete** — es una dep opcional que el operador instala y pinea. Ver\n`examples/linters.yaml.example`.\n\n```bash\npython runners/linter_gate.py linters.yaml [root]   # exit 0 limpio · 1 findings · 2 config/entorno inválido\n```\n\n**Dogfooding:** el propio repo se gatea con su `linters.yaml` de raíz (`ruff==0.15.20`, `required: true`,\nexcluye `fixtures/`+`examples/`+`ccdd.py`, ignora `E731`/`E402`) — paso bloqueante del CI (`.github/workflows/test.yml`).\n\n## Metodología KDD","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#362","metadata":{"content":"ithub/workflows/test.yml`).\n\n## Metodología KDD\n\nEl repo se desarrolla con **KDD (Knowledge-Driven Development)**: modela el contexto con\n[Open Knowledge Format](https://github.com/MauricioPerera/KDD) (OKF) y gobierna el desarrollo con\n**CCDD** (task-contracts + gates deterministas). El conocimiento vive en [`knowledge/`](knowledge/)\n(nodos OKF: `OKF-SPEC.md`, `architecture/`, `concepts/`, `contracts/`) y las reglas del ciclo de vida\nen [`.agents/AGENTS.md`](.agents/AGENTS.md) + la skill\n[`.agents/skills/kdd-okf-ccdd-hybrid/`](.agents/skills/kdd-okf-ccdd-hybrid/) (puente en\n[`AGENTS.md`](AGENTS.md)).","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#363","metadata":{"content":"d-hybrid/) (puente en\n[`AGENTS.md`](AGENTS.md)).\n\nUn **task-contract híbrido** es un nodo OKF (`type: 'Task Contract'`) con frontmatter CCDD\n(`task`, `intent`, `target`, `signature`, `budget`, `tests`, `test_command`, `deps_allowed`,\n`forbids`) + 7 secciones canónicas. Ejemplo real y validado:\n[`knowledge/contracts/kdd-sample-slugify.md`](knowledge/contracts/kdd-sample-slugify.md)\n(`slugify` pura en `src/kdd_sample/slugify.py`).\n\nSe valida en **dos niveles**, ambos deterministas (sin LLM):\n\n```bash\n# Nivel 1 — frontmatter + secciones + examples; y el test_command del contrato en verde.\npython scripts/validate_contracts.py knowledge/contracts","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#364","metadata":{"content":"cripts/validate_contracts.py knowledge/contracts\n\n# Nivel 2 nativo — el gate CCDD real de este repo (lint del contrato: forma + semántica).\npython runners/tc_lint.py knowledge/contracts/kdd-sample-slugify.md   # -> \"ok\": true\n```\n\nEl paso de Nivel 1 corre en CI (`.github/workflows/test.yml`, bloqueante). Plantilla y spec del\nformato híbrido: <https://github.com/MauricioPerera/KDD>.","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#365","metadata":{"content":"íbrido: <https://github.com/MauricioPerera/KDD>.\n\n**Campo `language` (opcional, multi-lenguaje).** Por defecto `python`. Con `language: python`\nla firma se valida con el AST nativo (preciso). Para otros lenguajes (`typescript`, `javascript`,\n`go`, …) `tc_lint` valida la firma por **aridad genérica** (cuenta de parámetros top-level y\nextracción de nombre, respetando `()[]{}<>` y comillas) y emite el warning `tc-signature-generic`\npara señalar que no hay parser nativo. `params_max` y el resto de reglas se aplican igual.\nSin el campo, el comportamiento es idéntico al actual (Python).\n\n## Conformancia multi-lenguaje","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#366","metadata":{"content":"actual (Python).\n\n## Conformancia multi-lenguaje\n\n`fixtures/conformance/` define un **oráculo congelado** de las 4 métricas (fixtures equivalentes\npor lenguaje + valores esperados). Todo backend debe reproducirlo: Python es el baseline y los\nbackends **tree-sitter** (TS/TSX/JS/Rust/Go/Java/C#/PHP/Ruby/Kotlin/C/Swift/C++) pasan la suite con métricas estructurales\nidénticas (`cyclomatic`/`nesting_depth`/`parameter_count`); solo `function_length` diverge por\nformato y se fija por-lenguaje. Un backend nuevo no se acepta hasta pasar\n`tests/test_conformance.py`. Ver\n[`fixtures/conformance/README.md`](fixtures/conformance/README.md).","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#367","metadata":{"content":"nce/README.md`](fixtures/conformance/README.md).\n\n**Multi-lenguaje hoy (métricas de complejidad):** Python nativo (sin deps) + TS/TSX/JS/Rust/Go/Java/C#/PHP/Ruby/Kotlin/C/Swift/C++\nvía tree-sitter (dep opcional: `pip install tree_sitter tree_sitter_typescript tree_sitter_rust\ntree_sitter_go tree_sitter_java tree_sitter_c_sharp tree_sitter_php tree_sitter_ruby tree_sitter_kotlin\ntree_sitter_c tree_sitter_swift tree_sitter_cpp`). El gate, el hook y\n`measure_complexity` miden esas extensiones igual que `.py` cuando las gramáticas están instaladas;\nsi no, esos archivos son no-op anunciado. Los checks de antipatrones (`gate-mutdef`, `gate-assert`,\n`gate-signature`, `gate-deps`, etc.) siguen siendo **Python-only** (AST nativo).\n\n## Integración GitHub (opcional, `integrations/github/`)","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#368","metadata":{"content":"ación GitHub (opcional, `integrations/github/`)\n\nCapa adaptadora **opcional**: el sustrato determinista no depende de GitHub. Sin ella, todo\nfunciona en local. Usa `gh` CLI; tokens por entorno, nunca en el repo.","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#369","metadata":{"content":"`gh` CLI; tokens por entorno, nunca en el repo.","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#37","metadata":{"content":"# Qué hay acá","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#370","metadata":{"content":"`gh` CLI; tokens por entorno, nunca en el repo.","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#371","metadata":{"content":"gh` CLI; tokens por entorno, nunca en el repo.","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#372","metadata":{"content":"h` CLI; tokens por entorno, nunca en el repo.","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#373","metadata":{"content":"` CLI; tokens por entorno, nunca en el repo.","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#374","metadata":{"content":"CLI; tokens por entorno, nunca en el repo.","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#375","metadata":{"content":"CLI; tokens por entorno, nunca en el repo.","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#376","metadata":{"content":"LI; tokens por entorno, nunca en el repo.","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#377","metadata":{"content":"I; tokens por entorno, nunca en el repo.","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#378","metadata":{"content":"; tokens por entorno, nunca en el repo.","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#379","metadata":{"content":"tokens por entorno, nunca en el repo.","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#38","metadata":{"content":"Qué hay acá","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#380","metadata":{"content":"tokens por entorno, nunca en el repo.","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#381","metadata":{"content":"okens por entorno, nunca en el repo.","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#382","metadata":{"content":"kens por entorno, nunca en el repo.","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#383","metadata":{"content":"ens por entorno, nunca en el repo.","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#384","metadata":{"content":"ns por entorno, nunca en el repo.","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#385","metadata":{"content":"s por entorno, nunca en el repo.","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#386","metadata":{"content":"por entorno, nunca en el repo.","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#387","metadata":{"content":"por entorno, nunca en el repo.","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#388","metadata":{"content":"or entorno, nunca en el repo.","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#389","metadata":{"content":"r entorno, nunca en el repo.","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#39","metadata":{"content":"Qué hay acá","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#390","metadata":{"content":"entorno, nunca en el repo.","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#391","metadata":{"content":"entorno, nunca en el repo.","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#392","metadata":{"content":"ntorno, nunca en el repo.","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#393","metadata":{"content":"torno, nunca en el repo.","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#394","metadata":{"content":"orno, nunca en el repo.","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#395","metadata":{"content":"rno, nunca en el repo.","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#396","metadata":{"content":"no, nunca en el repo.","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#397","metadata":{"content":"o, nunca en el repo.","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#398","metadata":{"content":", nunca en el repo.","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#399","metadata":{"content":"nunca en el repo.","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#4","metadata":{"content":"rar el MCP en un cliente (Claude Code / Desktop)\n\n```json\n{ \"mcpServers\": { \"ccdd\": { \"command\": \"ccdd-mcp\" } } }\n```\n\n> El **modo desde el repo** (`python runners/<x>.py`, `pip install -e .`) sigue funcionando\n> para desarrollo — ver [Quickstart](#quickstart) e\n> [Instalación como paquete](#instalación-como-paquete-console-scripts).\n\n---\n\n## La idea en una frase\n\nEl **modelo grande** planifica y audita; el **modelo pequeño** (local/barato) implementa;\nun **gate determinista** decide. El grande solo entra a autorar la tarea, auditar los tests\ny rescatar cuando el chico se atasca. La inteligencia difusa va en el LLM; el control y el\nveredicto van en código que no se puede engañar.\n\n## Qué hay acá","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#40","metadata":{"content":"ué hay acá","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#400","metadata":{"content":"nunca en el repo.","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#401","metadata":{"content":"unca en el repo.","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#402","metadata":{"content":"nca en el repo.","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#403","metadata":{"content":"ca en el repo.","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#404","metadata":{"content":"a en el repo.","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#405","metadata":{"content":"en el repo.","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#406","metadata":{"content":"en el repo.","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#407","metadata":{"content":"n el repo.","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#408","metadata":{"content":"el repo.","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#409","metadata":{"content":"el repo.","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#41","metadata":{"content":"é hay acá","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#410","metadata":{"content":"l repo.","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#411","metadata":{"content":"repo.","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#412","metadata":{"content":"repo.","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#413","metadata":{"content":"epo.","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#414","metadata":{"content":"po.","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#415","metadata":{"content":"o.","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#416","metadata":{"content":".","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#417","metadata":{"content":"- `reporter.py` — toma el JSON de `task_gate`/`complexity_gate` y genera un comentario Markdown\n  determinista (PASS/FAIL, métricas vs budget, motivo). Idempotente: actualiza un comentario\n  \"marcado\" en vez de spamear. Offline imprime el Markdown; `--post` lo publica vía `gh`.\n- `ci_gate.py` + `.github/workflows/ccdd-gate.yml` — **GitHub Action**: en cada PR descubre los\n  task-contracts afectados (el `.md` o su `target`), corre `tc_lint` + `task_gate` y **bloquea el\n  merge** (exit 1) si el veredicto no pasa; publica el resumen como comentario idempotente vía el\n  Reporter.","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#418","metadata":{"content":"n como comentario idempotente vía el\n  Reporter. Además corre **no-opcionalmente** `audit_composition` y `audit_annotations`\n  project-wide y `mutation_audit` sobre los contratos afectados: composición sin gatear, anotaciones\n  sin importar o mutantes sobrevivientes también ponen el check en rojo (lo que el autor tiende a\n  saltar cuando es opt-in, acá no se puede saltar). Sin LLM, sin secretos (usa el `GH_TOKEN` del\n  runner). **Copiable a un repo consumidor**: copia `.github/workflows/ccdd-gate.yml` e\n  `integrations/github/` (o vendoriza/instala ccdd-gate) y activa branch protection sobre el check\n  `ccdd-gate`.\n- `scaffold.py` — genera el esqueleto de un task-contract desde un issue (`--issue owner/repo#N`\n  o `--from-json` offline).","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#419","metadata":{"content":"--issue owner/repo#N`\n  o `--from-json` offline). Captura la intención (título/cuerpo/labels) con placeholders `TODO`;\n  el resultado es **incompleto a propósito** (`tc_lint` lo marca, no falsamente verde).\n- `lifecycle.py` — conecta el **orquestador** con el ciclo de vida del issue: un issue `ccdd:ready`\n  con gate verde abre un PR enlazado (`Closes #N`) y pasa a `ccdd:in-review`; si escala → `ccdd:escalated`;\n  si ni el grande pasa → `ccdd:needs-split`. El loop del orquestador no sabe de GitHub (recibe un\n  callback opcional `on_result`); sin él, corre igual en local.","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#42","metadata":{"content":"hay acá","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#420","metadata":{"content":"onal `on_result`); sin él, corre igual en local. Transiciones de label deterministas y reversibles.\n- `decompose.py` — materializa task-contracts atómicos como **sub-issues** de un issue padre\n  (epic/feature), con vínculo bidireccional y marker idempotente (re-ejecutar no duplica). No\n  decide la descomposición (la decide el autor): solo la materializa.\n- `link.py` — vínculo bidireccional contrato↔issue: `status --contract` (estado + labels) o\n  `status --issue owner/repo#N` (contratos que lo referencian), y `sync-labels` (refleja el estado\n  como labels `ccdd:*`, idempotente, sin pisar labels ajenas). El campo `issue` del front-matter es\n  opcional; `tc_lint` valida su formato (regla `tc-issue-ref`) sin romper contratos sin él.\n\n## Benchmarks","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#421","metadata":{"content":"f`) sin romper contratos sin él.\n\n## Benchmarks\n\nVer [`BENCHMARKS.md`](BENCHMARKS.md). En resumen: el gate determinista cuesta **0 tokens** y\nsu lógica es **sub-milisegundo** (`python benchmarks/bench_gate.py`). La economía grande/pequeño\nestá medida y **honestamente etiquetada como ilustrativa** — gana por reuso/volumen, no en el\none-shot trivial (ahí es más caro).\n\n## Honestidades (léelas antes de creerle a nadie)","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#422","metadata":{"content":"Honestidades (léelas antes de creerle a nadie)","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#423","metadata":{"content":"Honestidades (léelas antes de creerle a nadie)","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#424","metadata":{"content":"onestidades (léelas antes de creerle a nadie)","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#425","metadata":{"content":"nestidades (léelas antes de creerle a nadie)","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#426","metadata":{"content":"estidades (léelas antes de creerle a nadie)","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#427","metadata":{"content":"stidades (léelas antes de creerle a nadie)","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#428","metadata":{"content":"tidades (léelas antes de creerle a nadie)","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#429","metadata":{"content":"idades (léelas antes de creerle a nadie)","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#43","metadata":{"content":"hay acá","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#430","metadata":{"content":"dades (léelas antes de creerle a nadie)","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#431","metadata":{"content":"ades (léelas antes de creerle a nadie)","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#432","metadata":{"content":"des (léelas antes de creerle a nadie)","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"README.md#433","metadata":{"content":"es (léelas antes de creerle a nadie)","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type